                                Skinny Table | Index Table | Main Table
                        -------------------------------------------------------------

    Skinny Table; - Skinny Table is combination of standard field and custom field, used to optimize performance for objects
                    with Large Data Volumes (LDV).

      Notes:- If we query standard field and custom field on object behind the seen join happens. as in salesforce standard
              field is having a separate table and custom field is having a separate table.After joining it return the record.
              if recod is more than 1 million performance got slow, agent feel bore so skinny table come in to picture. salesforce
              customer support will create the skinny table we need to provide the details of field which all field needs to be
              added. later if want to add more field need to connect again to the customer support.once the skinny table got
              created and if we query it will go to the skinny table if all field is added in to the skinny table it fetch from
              the skinny table else go to the main table like need join and take time.
    Points: -
            1. A Skinny Table can hold a maximum of 200 columns (fields).
            2. Skinny Tables completely ignore and exclude soft-deleted records that is availbe in recyclebin.
            3. skinny table does not support formula, long text area, Rich text area, picklist etc.

*****************************************************************************************************************************
                                          Index Table
                                    ------------------------
    Index Table: - Index Table is a highly specialized database table used by the platform to dramatically speed up data 
                    retrieval for queries, reports, and list views. Instead of storing full object records with all 
                    their custom fields, the Index Table isolates and stores only one specific field value paired directly
                    with its unique Salesforce Recordid, standard field,custom unique field and external id field.

      Notes:- process of addingcustom field to the index table: - Need to make the field unique or make external field.
              we have record Id in Index table this know the record where it is available no need to search details one by one

  Points: - 
          1. You can only have a maximum of 25 custom fields marked as External ID or Unique per object. If you need 
              more fields indexed beyond that, you must ask Salesforce Support to create a Custom Index.

          2. Selectivity Threshold: Standard Indexed fields must return less than 30% of the total records.
                                   - Custom Indexed fields must return less than 10% of the total records.
             If a query returns more than these percentages, Salesforce ignores the Index Table and scans the main table.


